
## AFK orchestrator

This repo uses [`afk-agent`](https://github.com/Mo-Tamim/afk-agent)
for issue-driven AFK ("away from keyboard") work.

### Issue tracker

`{{TRACKER}}` on `{{REPO}}`; the orchestrator shells out to `{{TRACKER_CLI}}`.
The AFK label vocabulary is defined in `.afk/labels.yml`.

### Phase lifecycle

```
PRD → decompose → children → (plan → implement → review → PR → CI → PR-review → merge)* → document → PRD closed
```

Every phase ends with one of `<promise>COMPLETE</promise>`,
`<promise>NO_CHANGES</promise>`, or `<promise>BLOCKED</promise>`.
See `.afk/skills/afk-workflow/SKILL.md`.

### Skills

When the active phase prompt names a skill, read it from
`.afk/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` (or from the user's installed copy of
the `afk-agent` bundle). The orchestrator never re-injects skill
contents into the prompt — load on demand.

### Daily commands

```bash
.afk/scripts/afk setup                 # one-time: create labels, sanity-check
.afk/scripts/afk decompose <PRD#>      # PRD → child issues
.afk/scripts/afk run                   # bounded-parallelism orchestrator (long-running)
.afk/scripts/afk run --once            # process current queue then exit
.afk/scripts/afk issue <N>             # drive one child end-to-end
.afk/scripts/afk status                # snapshot of every in-flight issue
.afk/scripts/afk dashboard             # live web dashboard (http://127.0.0.1:8765)
.afk/scripts/afk dashboard --background  # detached; use --stop to halt
.afk/scripts/afk stop-notify           # silence any active wake-up alarm
```

### Telemetry

Every significant lifecycle transition appends one JSON line to
`.afk/logs/events.ndjson` (kinds: `orchestrator_start`,
`runner_spawn`, `issue_start`, `phase_start`, `agent_spawn`,
`phase_end`, `issue_end`, `runner_reap`, `orchestrator_exit`). The
dashboard consumes this stream. Best-effort — failures here never
change orchestrator behaviour.

### Driving from chat

If the active session is an interactive chat (Cursor sidebar, Copilot
Chat, Claude Code, …), prefer the `/afk-run` skill — it wraps the same
commands above, but knows how to interpret sentinels for the user and
how to spawn a long `afk run` detached when the chat tool's time limit
isn't enough. The skill is at `.afk/skills/afk-run/SKILL.md`.

If the session is a terminal or CI, use the bash commands directly.
